<p>When passing data across jobs, it is usually necessary to first set the step output via <code>ATOMGIT_OUTPUT</code>, then map the step output to the job output via <code>jobs.&amp;lt;job_id&amp;gt;.outputs</code>, and finally have downstream jobs retrieve it via <code>needs.&amp;lt;job_id&amp;gt;.outputs.&amp;lt;output_name&amp;gt;</code>.</p>
<h2 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_pqwd" id="4-atomgit_path-appending-command-directories-to-path">4. <code>ATOMGIT_PATH</code>: Appending Command Directories to PATH<a href="#4-atomgit_path-appending-command-directories-to-path" class="hash-link" aria-label="4-atomgit_path-appending-command-directories-to-path的直接链接" title="4-atomgit_path-appending-command-directories-to-path的直接链接">​</a></h2>
<h3 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_pqwd" id="purpose-2">Purpose<a href="#purpose-2" class="hash-link" aria-label="Purpose的直接链接" title="Purpose的直接链接">​</a></h3>
<p><code>ATOMGIT_PATH</code> is used to append a directory to the system <code>PATH</code>, so that subsequent steps or actions can directly call the executable files in that directory. After writing, the current step cannot immediately access the updated PATH, only subsequent steps can access it.</p>
<h3 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_pqwd" id="use-cases-2">Use Cases<a href="#use-cases-2" class="hash-link" aria-label="Use Cases的直接链接" title="Use Cases的直接链接">​</a></h3>
<p>Suitable for temporarily installing CLI, script tools, or build tools in the pipeline and allowing subsequent steps to directly call them.</p>
